    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of structural lumber product composed of a wood core with several layers of wood veneer bonded to the front and back by durable adhesive known as laminating stock. Glue-laminated timber beams are used as an alternative to steel beams in construction due in part to the relative energy-efficiency of their manufacture which produces far less greenhouse gas emissions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
